/group      Manipulate groups of hooks

Syntax:
    /group
    /group <hookname>
    /group -l <groupname>

Options:
    -l      List hooks belonging to group <name>

Notes:
    With no arguments, /group will list all defined groups.  With a hook name 
    passed, /group will list all groups the named hook is a member of.

Examples:
    /group -l "Dirt commands"

See Also:
    /hook, /enable, /disable
